      <a href="/contact-for-alfa-laval-centrifuges/" class="shrink-0 inline-block bg-gold text-white font-bold px-6 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-gold/90 transition-colors text-center">
        Request a Quote &rarr;
      </a>
    </div>

    <!-- DMPX Series Comparison -->
    <h2 id="dmpx-series-comparison">How the DMPX-010 Fits the DMPX Series</h2>
    <p>
      The DMPX series spans a wide range of throughputs to match every application scale. The <strong>DMPX-010</strong> (this page) is the entry-level model at ~7 GPM diesel, ideal when space and flow requirements are modest. Moving up, the
      <a href="/dmpx-014-self-cleaning-3-phase-disc-stack-centrifuge/">DMPX-014</a>
      roughly doubles throughput to ~13 GPM, while the
      <a href="/centrifuges/dmpx-028/">DMPX-028</a>
      (~20–26 GPM) handles medium industrial volumes. The
      <a href="/centrifuges/dmpx-042/">DMPX-042</a>
      (~32–47 GPM) and
      <a href="/centrifuges/dmpx-070/">DMPX-070</a>
      (~59–72 GPM) serve large-scale industrial and power-generation applications.
      All DMPX models share the same automatic self-cleaning bowl technology and continuous three-phase separation capability. Visit our
      <a href="/disc-stack-centrifuge/">disc stack centrifuge overview</a>
      to compare models side by side, or <a href="/contact-for-alfa-laval-centrifuges/">contact us</a> to discuss your application.
    </p>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <h2 id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <details class="border-l-4 border-gold/40 pl-4 mb-4 not-prose">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer py-2">What is the throughput of the DMPX-010 centrifuge?</summary>
      <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        The DMPX-010 processes approximately 7 GPM of diesel fuel at rated conditions and up to ~12 GPM under ideal, low-viscosity conditions. Lube oil (R&amp;O) throughput is ~4 GPM and steam turbine oil is ~8 GPM. HFO can be processed at 4–7 GPM depending on viscosity grade.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details class="border-l-4 border-gold/40 pl-4 mb-4 not-prose">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer py-2">What applications is the DMPX-010 best suited for?</summary>
      <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        The DMPX-010 is purpose-built for compact and portable installations: small marine vessel <a href="/diesel-centrifuge/">diesel polishing</a>, remote-site <a href="/waste-oil-centrifuge/">waste oil</a> reclamation, compact hydraulic oil maintenance, and portable lube oil purification where space and weight are at a premium.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details class="border-l-4 border-gold/40 pl-4 mb-4 not-prose">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer py-2">How does the DMPX-010 compare to larger Dolphin DMPX models?</summary>
      <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        The DMPX-010 is the smallest model in the DMPX series with a 0.16-gallon sludge bowl and ~3.5–5 HP motor. The <a href="/dmpx-014-self-cleaning-3-phase-disc-stack-centrifuge/">DMPX-014</a> roughly doubles diesel throughput (~13 GPM), while the <a href="/centrifuges/dmpx-028/">DMPX-028</a> (~20–26 GPM) and <a href="/centrifuges/dmpx-042/">DMPX-042</a> (~32–47 GPM) serve progressively larger industrial applications.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details class="border-l-4 border-gold/40 pl-4 mb-4 not-prose">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer py-2">What is the difference between the DMPX-010 and a manual-clean centrifuge?</summary>
      <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        The DMPX-010 is a <a href="/disc-stack-centrifuge/">self-cleaning centrifuge</a> — it ejects accumulated solids automatically without stopping. A manual-clean unit like the <a href="/centrifuges/dmb-004/">DMB-004</a> requires periodic shutdown and bowl disassembly. The DMPX-010 is ideal for continuous unattended operation where cleaning downtime is not acceptable.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details class="border-l-4 border-gold/40 pl-4 mb-4 not-prose">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer py-2">Can the DMPX-010 handle HFO heavy fuel oil?</summary>
      <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        The DMPX-010 is not rated for HFO 380 cSt. It processes HFO 30 cSt at ~7 GPM and HFO 180 cSt at ~4 GPM. For heavy bunker fuel at full viscosity, the larger <a href="/centrifuges/dmpx-028/">DMPX-028</a> or <a href="/centrifuges/dmpx-042/">DMPX-042</a> models are more appropriate. <a href="/contact-for-alfa-laval-centrifuges/">Contact us</a> for fluid-specific sizing.
      </p>
    </details>

  </article>

